    rationale: "Rome IV criteria for functional constipation require that at least 2 of the specified symptoms (fewer than 3 BM/week, straining in \u226525% of defecations, lumpy/hard stools in \u226525%, sensation of incomplete evacuation in \u226525%, sensation of anorectal obstruction in \u226525%, or manual maneuvers to facilitate defecation in \u226525%) be present for \u226512 weeks in the preceding 6 months. The symptoms do not need to be continuous for 6 months \u2014 they must total at least 12 weeks within that 6-month window. 4 and 8 weeks are insufficient to meet the chronic threshold.",
