    rationale: "Shifting dullness is the percussion maneuver used to confirm free peritoneal fluid (ascites). The examiner percusses from the umbilicus toward the flank until dullness is detected, marks the point, then asks the patient to roll to the opposite side and repercusses \u2014 if the dullness shifts to the new dependent area, free fluid is confirmed. A fluid wave (transmitted impulse across the abdomen) is another test for ascites but requires an assistant and is less sensitive for small volumes. Deep palpation for a ballotable mass assesses for organomegaly, not ascites. Abdominal girth measurement tracks changes over time but does not confirm the nature of the distension.",
