    rationale: "Villous adenomas are characterized by their ability to secrete large volumes of mucus and fluid, producing a secretory diarrhea that can cause significant electrolyte losses \u2014 particularly hypokalemia and hyponatremia. This is sometimes called 'McKittrick-Wheelock syndrome' in extreme cases. Tubular adenomas rarely secrete mucus. Hyperplastic polyps are benign and non-secretory. Carcinoid tumors cause serotonin-mediated effects (flushing, diarrhea) but not mucus hypersecretion.",
