    rationale: "In a patient with established Crohn's disease, blood-streaked mucus in stool raises concern for an active IBD flare with significant mucosal inflammation, or \u2014 given the chronic inflammatory background \u2014 early dysplastic change or colorectal malignancy. Mucus with blood in the context of IBD should not be dismissed as functional. IBS does not cause bloody stool. Villous adenoma is possible but less likely in a 32-year-old with known IBD. Infectious gastroenteritis is possible but the known IBD history makes IBD-related pathology the priority concern.",
